INSERT INTO `articles` VALUES (9, 'Ruben Amorim tactics, formation and playing style: How could Man Utd line up under new head coach?', 'Man Utd boss Ruben Amorim was successful in Portugal but what is his philosophy and what might \'Amorim-ball\' look like at Old Trafford?', '2024-12-09 00:00:00', 'Erik ten Hag\'s inability to implement a discernible style of play at Manchester United was one of his biggest problems, so it is hardly surprising that, in Ruben Amorim, the club have chosen a manager with a clear identity as the Dutchman\'s successor.\r\n\r\nAcross a four-year spell at Sporting Lisbon, during which he has won two Portuguese league titles and two league cups - having previously won the league cup with Braga - the 39-year-old put a stamp on the side which has remained consistent despite player turnover.\r\n\r\nSponsored link\r\nErik ten Hag\'s inability to implement a discernible style of play at Manchester United was one of his biggest problems, so it is hardly surprising that, in Ruben Amorim, the club have chosen a manager with a clear identity as the Dutchman\'s successor.\r\n\r\nAcross a four-year spell at Sporting Lisbon, during which he has won two Portuguese league titles and two league cups - having previously won the league cup with Braga - the 39-year-old put a stamp on the side which has remained consistent despite player turnover.\r\n\r\nSponsored link\r\nErik ten Hag\'s inability to implement a discernible style of play at Manchester United was one of his biggest problems, so it is hardly surprising that, in Ruben Amorim, the club have chosen a manager with a clear identity as the Dutchman\'s successor.\r\n\r\nAcross a four-year spell at Sporting Lisbon, during which he has won two Portuguese league titles and two league cups - having previously won the league cup with Braga - the 39-year-old put a stamp on the side which has remained consistent despite player turnover.', 3, 'Sport', 'nobody', NULL);
INSERT INTO `articles` VALUES (10, 'Man Utd: No quick fix for Ruben Amorim as United show familiar flaws in draw with Ipswich', 'Ruben Amorim took charge of his first Manchester United match as they played Ipswich at Portman Road; goalkeeper Andre Onana came to their rescue to earn them a point from a 1-1 draw; Amad Diallo took his chance but familiar failings were on show from his team-mates', '2024-12-18 00:00:00', 'As the first whistle blew to signal a new era at Portman Road for United, you could sense the anticipation in the away end. Football is about being able to dream. That brighter days could be around the corner.\r\n\r\nJust look at Ipswich Town - this time two years ago, they were drawing 1-1 with Fleetwood Town in League One.\r\n\r\n\r\nSponsored Links\r\nRecommended byWhat is Outbrain\r\nVietnam to snuff out vaping in 2025, following Thailand and Singapore\r\nVietnam to snuff out vaping in 2025, following Thailand and Singapore\r\n(Nikkei Asia)\r\nColeen Rooney reveals what husband Wayne really thinks of her entering the jungle\r\nColeen Rooney reveals what husband Wayne really thinks of her entering the jungle\r\n(Ohmymag)\r\nHarry Styles: Here are all the million dollar properties he\'s owned across the world\r\nHarry Styles: Here are all the million dollar properties he\'s owned across the world\r\n(NEWS/OhMyMag.co.uk)\r\nLiam Payne set aside massive fortune for son Bear: \'My money is for him\'\r\nLiam Payne set aside massive fortune for son Bear: \'My money is for him\'\r\n(NEWS/OhMyMag.co.uk)\r\nNomura execs give up pay after employee allegedly tried to kill clients\r\nNomura execs give up pay after employee allegedly tried to kill clients\r\n(Nikkei Asia)\r\nLetter from Nikkei Asia\'s editor: High political drama in South Korea and the Philippines\r\nLetter from Nikkei Asia\'s editor: High political drama in South Korea and the Philippines\r\n(Nikkei Asia)\r\nSouth Korea\'s martial law shock: 5 things to know\r\nSouth Korea\'s martial law shock: